Windows
=======

* python

Get from http://www.python.org/download/ .
Get the file "Python 2.7.3 Windows Installer".

* setuptools

Get from https://pypi.python.org/pypi/setuptools#downloads
Take setuptools-0.6c11.win32-py2.7.exe 

* pip

next start a command prompt and execute:

cd c:\Python27\Scripts
easy_install pip
keep the shell open

* numpy

pip install numpy

* pyside

pip install pyside

* beautifulsoup4

pip install beautifulsoup4

* pyopengl

from https://pypi.python.org/pypi/PyOpenGL/3.0.2

take PyOpenGL-3.0.2.win32.exe

* pyopengl-accelerate

from https://pypi.python.org/pypi/PyOpenGL-accelerate/3.0.2

take PyOpenGL-accelerate-3.0.2.win32-py2.7.exe

* pyv8

from http://code.google.com/p/pyv8/downloads/list

take PyV8-1.0-preview-r443.win32-py2.7.exe

* python imaging

from http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/
take "Python Imaging Library 1.1.7 for Python 2.7"
